lead_paragraph: Noname, the Chicago rapper known for her collaborations with Chance the Rapper, is in The New York Times headquarters to perform some songs and answer questions from the online audience. Joe Coscarelli and Andrew Chow, who cover music for The Times, are in the room with her and will be addressing your questions and sharing their thoughts throughout. Join in the conversation here.
